com.kaazing.net.ws.amqp

Class AmqpClientFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kaazing.net.ws.amqp.AmqpClientFactory

  • public class AmqpClientFactory
extends Object
    AmqClientFactory is used to create instances of AmqpClient. Also, it is used to access the WebSocketFactory used to create the underlying WebSocket connection over which AMQP 0-9-1 protocol will be run. The WebSocketFactory can be used to set connection-timeout, challenge handlers, redirect policy, etc. These properties/characteristics set on the WebSocketFactory will be inherited by the WebSocket instances that are created using the factory.
